{
  "stem": "26142.14",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] It's a Christian religion, but they kept the Sabbath.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I don't understand it too well, but anyway, the people were friendly to us over there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I remember where we stayed in one of the barns, when I talked to the owner, I asked him if he is able to sell me some linen, pieces of linen, so that we could at least have dry linen because socks we didn't have.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We would just tie around the linen in the shoe.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "At least you had dry linen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they did that for us in that winter.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The city changed hands about two, three times.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Germans would be pushed back, then the Germans would push the Russians back.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a very, very bad time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "From after we got finished-- after we got finished cutting down this forest, we tried to somehow get in touch with the partisans because we were considering of deserting in there.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it turned out that we did get contact with them through the local people, but they would-- they would not accept anybody unless we could bring with us weapons.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Without weapons, they would not accept.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we had no way of getting not even a revolver or anything because we didn't have it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was on the other side of the Bug River.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was assumed that if-- if the Germans-- if the Russians would push the Germans back behind the Bug River, they would put up-- they would put up a stand at the river because it's a fairly big river and that would be a good line-- a line of defense.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was the one that happened to be out on the outhouse when this happened, and he survived the war.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
